  "prompt": "What is a suitable inpatient drug and alcohol rehab center in Cherokee County AL?",
  "response": "While I don't have access to real-time data or specific facility details, I can suggest some general steps to help you find a suitable inpatient drug and alcohol rehab center in Cherokee County, AL:\n\n1. **Local Resources**: Contact local health departments or community health organizations for recommendations on rehab centers.\n\n2. **Online Directories**: Websites such as SAMHSA (Substance Abuse and Mental Health Services Administration) provide a searchable database of treatment facilities by location.\n\n3. **Medical Professionals**: Speak with a healthcare provider or therapist for referrals to trusted rehab centers.\n\n4. **Support Groups**: Organizations like Alcoholics Anonymous (AA) or Narcotics Anonymous (NA) often have resources and can suggest local treatment centers.\n\n5. **Consult Reviews**: Look at online reviews and testimonials to gauge the quality of care provided by local facilities.\n\n6. **Insurance Provider**: Check with your insurance company to find out which rehab centers are covered under your plan.\n\nWhen considering a facility, it's important to assess factors such as the type of programs offered, the qualifications of the staff, treatment modalities, and aftercare support. Ensure the facility aligns with your specific needs and preferences.",
